    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Isaiah",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 2,
        "summary": "Isaiah sees the latter-day temple, gathering of Israel, and millennial judgment and peace\u2014The proud and wicked will be brought low at the Second Coming\u2014Compare 2\u00a0Nephi 12.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "The word that Isaiah the son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isaiah chapters 2\u201314 are quoted from the brass plates by Nephi in 2\u00a0Ne. 12\u201324; there are some differences in wording which should be noted.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 20
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0khazah, meaning \u201cenvisioned.\u201d It means Isaiah received his message through a vision from the Lord.",
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And it shall come to pass in the last days, that the mountain of the Lord's house shall be established in the top of the mountains, and shall be exalted above the hills; and all nations shall flow unto it.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Last Days.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 13:2; Micah 4:1 (1\u20133).",
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jerusalem, New.",
                        "start": 76,
                        "end": 81
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Dispensations; Restoration of the Gospel.",
                        "start": 91,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Kgs. 8:41 (41\u201342). TG\u00a0Israel, Mission of; Nations.",
                        "start": 178,
                        "end": 185
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And many people shall go and say, Come ye, and let us go up to the mountain of the Lord, to the house of the God of Jacob; and he will teach us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths: for out of Zion shall go forth the law, and the word of the Lord from Jerusalem.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Millennium, Preparing a People for.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 56
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 48:1; Isa. 30:29; 3\u00a0Ne. 20:22; D&C 84:2 (2\u20134).",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Temple.",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 101
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Missionary Work; Teaching.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 140
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 33:20. TG\u00a0Kingdom of God, on Earth; Zion.",
                        "start": 199,
                        "end": 203
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0teaching, or doctrine. TG\u00a0God, Law of; Mission of Latter-day Saints.",
                        "start": 223,
                        "end": 226
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And he shall judge among the nations, and shall rebuke many people: and they shall beat their swords into plowshares, and their spears into pruninghooks: nation shall not lift up sword against nation, neither shall they learn war any more.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Judge.",
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 18
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Millennium; Peace; War.",
                        "start": 226,
                        "end": 229
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "O house of Jacob, come ye, and let us walk in the light of the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Walking with God.",
                        "start": 38,
                        "end": 42
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Jesus Christ, Light of the World.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 55
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore thou hast forsaken thy people the house of Jacob, because they be replenished from the east, and are soothsayers like the Philistines, and they please themselves in the children of strangers.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0are filled, supplied with teachings, alien beliefs. Ps. 106:35.",
                        "start": 73,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sorcery.",
                        "start": 111,
                        "end": 122
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0strike hands with, or make covenant with.",
                        "start": 154,
                        "end": 174
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 864
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 107,
                        "end": 110
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their land also is full of silver and gold, neither is there any end of their treasures; their land is also full of horses, neither is there any end of their chariots:",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 132,
                        "end": 144
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Their land also is full of idols; they worship the work of their own hands, that which their own fingers have made:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel; Idolatry.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust Not in the Arm of Flesh; Worship.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 46
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the mean man boweth down, and the great man humbleth himself: therefore forgive them not.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0ordinary man.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 12:9.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Enter into the rock, and hide thee in the dust, for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "The lofty looks of man shall be humbled, and the haughtiness of men shall be bowed down, and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 46:10 (7\u201311); Isa. 28:5.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 124
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 52:6; Hosea 2:16 (14\u201323); Zech. 9:16.",
                        "start": 133,
                        "end": 136
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "For the day of the Lord of hosts shall be upon every one that is proud and lofty, and upon every one that is lifted up; and he shall be brought low:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Day of the Lord.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Pride.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 70
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Job 40:11.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 147
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 41
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 64
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 108
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon all the cedars of Lebanon, that are high and lifted up, and upon all the oaks of Bashan,",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 31:3.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 36,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon all the high mountains, and upon all the hills that are lifted up,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon every high tower, and upon every fenced wall,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And upon all the ships of Tarshish, and upon all pleasant pictures.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "The Greek (Septuagint) version has one phrase that the Hebrew does not, and the Hebrew has one phrase that the Greek does not; but 2\u00a0Ne. 12:16 has both. Ps. 48:7; Ezek. 27:25.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 3
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the loftiness of man shall be bowed down, and the haughtiness of men shall be made low: and the Lord alone shall be exalted in that day.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Haughtiness.",
                        "start": 54,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And the idols he shall utterly abolish.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Idolatry.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 13
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And they shall go into the holes of the rocks, and into the caves of the earth, for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty, when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rev. 6:15.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Courage; Fearful.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 88
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "In that day a man shall cast his idols of silver, and his idols of gold, which they made each one for himself to worship, to the moles and to the bats;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0cast away.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 97
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "To go into the clefts of the rocks, and into the tops of the ragged rocks, for fear of the Lord, and for the glory of his majesty, when he ariseth to shake terribly the earth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Cease ye from man, whose breath is in his nostrils: for wherein is he to be accounted of?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0Cease depending on mortal man; he is of little power compared to God. Moses 1:10.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Trust Not in the Arm of Flesh.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 63
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 34
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}